http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/P.-Jayarajan-moves-anticipatory-bail-plea/article13995224.ece

Communist Party of India (Marxist) district unit secretary P. Jayarajan moved an anticipatory bail application in the District and Sessions Court at Thalassery on Monday alleging a move to arrest him and harass him by the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) team probing into the murder of Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS) functionary E. Manoj at Kathirur on September 1, 2014.Response to fresh noticeThe anticipatory bail application was moved in response to a fresh notice served by the Central Bureau of Investigation directing him to appear before the investigating officers at the Rest House at Thalassery at 11 a.m. on January 12.Earlier requestTo another notice sent by the CBI on January 5, Mr. Jayarajan sent request to exempt him from appearing before the CBI team on January 6 citing personal inconveniences.Harassment fearedMr. Jayarajanâ€™s counsel K. Viswan said that the anticipatory bail application was moved on the basis of an apprehension of arrest and harassment of Mr. Jayarajan by the CBI team.Political agendaHe said that the application also noted that there was a move by the Bharatiya Janata Party and the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS) to use the CBI to implement their political agenda. Though Mr. Jayarajan had not bee named an accused in the murder case, his client had the apprehension that he might be arrested when he appeared before the team, Mr. Viswan said.The bail application would be heard by the court on January 12.